This release contains the first release (r1) of:

-- The Hitchhiker's Guide to Adaptive Dynamics, an introduction to Adaptive Dynamics. 

-- The AdaptiveDynamics package for Mathematics which generates
   pairwise invasibility and trait evolution plots.

No installation should be necessary; just open "example.nb" and look through it. 
The Hitchhiker's Guide to Adaptive Dynamics is the file hitcchikers_guide.pdf and
the associated sources can be found in the directory tex/. 

The guide is licensed under the GNU Free Documentation License and the Mathematica
package under the GNU Public License. The specific terms are given in the files 
FDL.TXT and GPL.TXT respectively. 

Enjoy! 
